From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christopher Ayers <brianboitano87@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 09:17:35 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] nvmoe: overlap batched miss fetches at queue depth 2-4
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The custom op now resolves all of an op's cache misses first (assigning
and pinning victim slots), then fetches them with up to NVMOE_QD
concurrent readers (default 4, the measured NVMe optimum for multi-MB
extents) — each reader gets a private slice of the bounce buffer, and
both pread and the backend tensor_set are thread-safe. Single-miss ops
(the common warm-decode case) keep the direct path.

Decode ops rarely batch more than one miss, but cold starts, prefill
expert sweeps, and small cache budgets do. Measured on Qwen3-30B-A3B
(CUDA, decode-only with cold start): 4GB cache 17.0 -> 21.3 tok/s
(+25%), 8GB 47.6 -> 53.1 tok/s (+12%); OLMoE cold fill 0.64 -> 0.48s,
heavy-eviction fetch total 2.6 -> 1.8s. Logits gates re-passed
bit-identical on CPU and CUDA, including under eviction (fetch order
doesn't touch values — same bytes into pinned slots).

Router-logit lookahead (fetching layer L+1's experts during layer L's
compute) remains the open prefetch stage; this change is the I/O-side
half it will build on.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
